		<title>Degree Completions Aliquam sequi</title>

		<content:encoded><![CDATA[Bacon ipsum dolor amet pastrami ham hock cow jerky swine. Frankfurter landjaeger pork loin tail kielbasa bresaola cow doner beef brisket chicken turducken alcatra. Doner fatback filet mignon jerky, swine sausage alcatra. Spare ribs ham picanha, swine sirloin pork chop cupim brisket tail.

&nbsp;

Ham beef doner, strip steak meatloaf meatball jowl biltong brisket. Cow pig picanha ribeye cupim. Ground round pork loin hamburger tongue filet mignon turkey cow bresaola tail drumstick leberkas landjaeger boudin shoulder. Jowl pastrami flank, ham sirloin beef ribs ball tip strip steak andouille sausage cupim salami picanha tail. Kevin shank biltong pork chop flank strip steak turducken kielbasa pork leberkas tail hamburger meatloaf fatback.

&nbsp;

Sirloin brisket ground round tenderloin cupim biltong. Picanha brisket biltong, tail ball tip andouille drumstick tongue pig pork belly salami pancetta. 		<content:encoded><![CDATA[Pork loin tail kielbasa bresaola cow doner beef brisket chicken turducken alcatra. Doner fatback filet mignon jerky, swine sausage alcatra. Spare ribs ham picanha, swine sirloin pork chop cupim brisket tail.

&nbsp;

Ham beef doner, strip steak meatloaf meatball jowl biltong brisket. Cow pig picanha ribeye cupim. Ground round pork loin hamburger tongue filet mignon turkey cow bresaola tail drumstick leberkas landjaeger boudin shoulder. Jowl pastrami flank, ham sirloin beef ribs ball tip strip steak andouille sausage cupim salami picanha tail. Kevin shank biltong pork chop flank strip steak turducken kielbasa pork leberkas tail hamburger meatloaf fatback.

&nbsp;

		<title>Novel Action Repertoires</title>
		<link>http://telelanguage.com/event/novel-action-repertoires/</link>

&nbsp;

Ham beef doner, strip steak meatloaf meatball jowl biltong brisket. Cow pig picanha ribeye cupim. Ground round pork loin hamburger tongue filet mignon turkey cow bresaola tail drumstick leberkas landjaeger boudin shoulder. Jowl pastrami flank, ham sirloin beef ribs ball tip strip steak andouille sausage cupim salami picanha tail. Kevin shank biltong pork chop flank strip steak turducken kielbasa pork leberkas tail hamburger meatloaf fatback.

&nbsp;

Sirloin brisket ground round tenderloin cupim biltong. Picanha brisket biltong, tail ball tip andouille drumstick tongue pig pork belly salami pancetta. Pork loin short loin spare ribs meatloaf pork chicken. Porchetta capicola ribeye biltong turkey pork loin ground round, hamburger salami fatback pork belly bresaola doner. Ball tip brisket pork loin, pork chop kielbasa spare ribs cupim capicola picanha tenderloin kevin filet mignon pastrami chuck.]]></content:encoded>

	<item>
		<title>Does my organization have to sign a long-term contract with Telelanguage?</title>
		<link>http://telelanguage.com/hrf_faq/question/</link>
		<pubDate>Tue, 19 Jul 2016 18:50:00 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[admin]]></dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://telelanguage.com/?post_type=hrf_faq&#038;p=1734</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[No. Telephonic interpretation services are billed month-to-month and you are only billed for the time you've utilized an interpreter. However, contracts that are agreed upon for a specific amount of time carry the benefit of a guaranteed rate for the duration of the contract.
]]></content:encoded>

	<item>
		<title>Can Telelanguage provide me with materials or equipment to assist with interpretation?</title>
		<link>http://telelanguage.com/hrf_faq/question-2/</link>
		<pubDate>Tue, 19 Jul 2016 18:55:35 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[admin]]></dc:creator>

		<content:encoded><![CDATA[Certainly. Telelanguage is happy to provide you with many different types of educational and reference materials to make your interpretation experience as easy and simple as possible. With our technological capabilities, we are able to utilize automated dialing features that ensure a fast connection time for all of our clients. 	<item>
		<title>What kind of training do you offer your interpreters?</title>
		<link>http://telelanguage.com/hrf_faq/kind-training-offer-interpreters/</link>
		<pubDate>Tue, 19 Jul 2016 19:47:18 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[admin]]></dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://telelanguage.com/?post_type=hrf_faq&#038;p=1749</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[Our interpreters are tested and trained in many different fields of expertise. We are proud to provide interpreters who are qualified to interpret in fields such as healthcare, insurance, finance, legal and many others. We require our interpreters to participate in several training and mentoring programs before they begin their careers with Telelanguage. Nationally accepted codes of ethics and standards of practice are routinely reviewed throughout the interpreter's training to ensure we are providing the most professional services possible.
]]></content:encoded>

	<item>
		<title>How do you handle confidential information?</title>
		<link>http://telelanguage.com/hrf_faq/handle-confidential-information/</link>
		<pubDate>Tue, 19 Jul 2016 19:49:16 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[admin]]></dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://telelanguage.com/?post_type=hrf_faq&#038;p=1751</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[Telelanguage interpreters abide by a strict Code of Ethics and Confidentiality. They are professionals who are bound not only by a professional code of ethics, but also by written company policies and procedures that prohibit them from divulging any information about an interpretation. All documents and notes used for an interpretation are promptly destroyed at the end of the interpretation.
]]></content:encoded>

	<item>
		<title>What does Software as a Service mean?</title>
		<link>http://telelanguage.com/hrf_faq/software-service-mean/</link>
		<pubDate>Tue, 19 Jul 2016 20:03:20 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[admin]]></dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://telelanguage.com/?post_type=hrf_faq&#038;p=1762</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[Software as a service, or SaaS, is a subscription-based usage structure which provides software applications for a usage fee instead of requiring users to purchase licenses. You can scale up your usage model based on a variety of service plans. You only pay for what you use and have the flexibility of upscaling or downsizing at any time. Usually, SaaS software subscriptions are provided for a monthly fee.
]]></content:encoded>

	<item>
		<title>What are the different user levels of the GIP?</title>
		<link>http://telelanguage.com/hrf_faq/different-user-levels-gip/</link>
		<pubDate>Tue, 19 Jul 2016 20:07:52 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[admin]]></dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://telelanguage.com/?post_type=hrf_faq&#038;p=1765</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<strong>Requester:</strong> Requesters can log in to view and schedule their interpreter requests, view and search existing appointments and even request specific interpreters. 
<strong>Interpreter:</strong> Interpreters are able to use the GIP to view their schedules and accept appointments online in real time. 
<strong>Scheduler:</strong> Your interpreter coordinators will have the ability to create new appointments and assign interpreters using this feature. 
<strong>Management:</strong> With the management platform, users can create and manage interpreter profiles. 
<strong>Executive:</strong> The executive platform gives a user full access to the accounting module, site administration tools and all levels of user password management.
]]></content:encoded>
		<excerpt:encoded><![CDATA[]]></excerpt:encoded>

		<title>How many interpreters, customers, and employees can access the platform at the same time?</title>

	<item>
		<title>What type of industries currently utilize the GIP?</title>
		<link>http://telelanguage.com/hrf_faq/type-industries-currently-utilize-gip/</link>
		<pubDate>Tue, 19 Jul 2016 20:31:59 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[admin]]></dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://telelanguage.com/?post_type=hrf_faq&#038;p=1772</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[A few of the industries we are currently providing services for include (but are not limited to) : 

* Foreign language interpretation service providers 
* Non-profit language service providers 
* Courts 
* Hospitals 
* American Sign Language providers 
* Universities 
* Translation providers with growing face-to-face demands 
* Corporations with limited English proficiency or deaf/hard of hearing employees
]]></content:encoded>

		<content:encoded><![CDATA[[vc_row css=".vc_custom_1475829567713{padding-top: 40px !important;padding-bottom: 50px !important;background-image: url(http://telelanguage.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/12/homepageImage1265x630_pins.png?id=1561) !important;}" el_class="first-rows"][vc_column][vc_column_text]
<div class="banner-text">
<h2>Superior Language Support
in Over 250 Languages.</h2>
<a class="learn_more" href="http://telelanguage.com/services/telephonic-interpretation/">LEARN MORE!</a>

[/vc_column_text][themeum_divider divider="border" repeat="repeat" border_style="none" border_width="0" margin_top="100" margin_bottom="0"][lms_feature_course count="4" class="course-settings" margintop="0"][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row css=".vc_custom_1467476066636{background-color: #373d67 !important;}" el_class="parallax-section forms-rows"][vc_column][contact-form-7 id="1554"][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row css=".vc_custom_1472500614347{margin-top: 40px !important;margin-bottom: 70px !important;}"][vc_column][vc_column_text]
<h1 style="text-align: center; font-size: 2em;">Telelanguage 2000 Interpreters 250 Languages</h1>
<strong>
</strong><span style="color: #767676; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;"><b>Telelanguage has been providing our customers with the highest quality of service since 1991.</b> We are a reliable and innovative leader in the language industry. We provide interpretation and translation services to over 1,400 organizations throughout the United States – across all industries.
</span>

<span style="color: #767676; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;">As one of the leading language service providers in the country, we know a thing or two about communication. From on-site interpretation to document translation, telephonic interpretation to video remote interpretation, we can handle any of your language requests – regardless of industry or organizational size.</span>

<span style="color: #767676; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;">With over 99% of our current clients happy to recommend us, you’ll see why we’ve continued to grow.<b> </b><strong>Please continue to look around to learn more about our history, capabilities, technology, and more. Affordable Care Act compliance: We can help! <a href="http://telelanguage.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/Telelanguage-supports-new-National-Health-Law.pdf">Click here to learn more.</a></strong></span>

<strong> </strong>[/vc_column_text][themeum_divider divider="border" repeat="repeat" border_style="none" border_width="0" margin_top="5" margin_bottom="0"][vc_row_inner el_class="services-boxes"][vc_column_inner width="1/3"][vc_column_text]<a href="http://telelanguage.com/services/telephonic-interpretation/"><img src="http://telelanguage.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/TelephonicInterpre.jpg" alt="TelephonicInterpre" /></a>
<h2>Telephonic Interpretation</h2>
Telelanguage is a leading provider of over-the-phone interpreter services to customers who require fast connections, superior trained and certified interpreters and individually customized rate plans.
<ul>
 	<li><span style="line-height: 1.5;">Fastest connection times in the industry</span></li>
 	<li><span style="line-height: 1.5;">Always competitive rates</span></li>
 	<li>Multiple location and real time transferring</li>
 	<li>24x7x365 customer service support</li>
</ul>
<a class="more-learn" href="http://telelanguage.com/services/telephonic-interpretation/">LEARN MORE!</a>[/vc_column_text][/vc_column_inner][vc_column_inner el_class="orange" width="1/3"][vc_column_text]<a href="http://telelanguage.com/services/on-site-interpretation/"><img src="http://telelanguage.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/OnsiteService.jpg" alt="OnsiteService" /></a>
<h2>On-Site Interpretation</h2>
Our On-Site Interpretation Service is a more appropriate solution for appointments planned in advance that may require the extra human interaction and visual contact of interpreter and the Non-English Speaking client.
<ul>
 	<li>99% appointment fulfillment rate</li>
 	<li>Secure on-line scheduling and verification</li>
 	<li>Real time usage and statistics reports</li>
 	<li>Highest levels of quality assurance</li>
</ul>
<a class="more-learn" href="http://telelanguage.com/services/on-site-interpretation/">LEARN MORE!</a>[/vc_column_text][/vc_column_inner][vc_column_inner el_class="red" width="1/3"][vc_column_text]<a href="http://telelanguage.com/services/video-remote-interpretation/"><img src="http://telelanguage.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/VideoRemoteInterpreting.jpg" alt="VideoRemoteInterpreting" /></a>
<h2>Video Remote Interpretation</h2>
It’s one thing to interpret words; it’s another thing to know that those words were understood. Our video remote interpretation services make it possible to:
<ul>
 	<li>Fills the gap between over-the-phone and on-site interpretation</li>
 	<li>State-of-the-art technology</li>
 	<li>Highly secure business class video connectivity platform</li>
</ul>
<a class="more-learn" href="http://telelanguage.com/services/video-remote-interpretation/">LEARN MORE!</a>[/vc_column_text][/vc_column_inner][/vc_row_inner][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row css=".vc_custom_1475254855394{margin-top: 30px !important;margin-bottom: 0px !important;padding-top: 60px !important;padding-bottom: 60px !important;background-image: url(http://telelanguage.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/12/SchedulingSoftware.jpg?id=2678) !important;}" el_class="scheduling-softwaress"][vc_column][vc_column_text]
<p style="text-align: center; margin-bottom: 25px;">Scheduling Software</p>
<p style="text-align: center; font-size: 1.2em !important;">Our on-demand Interpreter management platform is specifically designed
for a wide variety of industries to better manage their interpretation services.</p>
<p style="text-align: center; margin-bottom: 50px;">14 Day FREE Trial - Schedule a Demo - Call: 1 (888) 983-5352 For More Info!</p>
<a class="learn-more" href="http://telelanguage.com/services/scheduling-software/">LEARN MORE!</a>[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][/vc_row]]]></content:encoded>

<h2>Introduction And History</h2>
Sirloin bresaola ball tip shank tail porchetta pork boudin filet mignon flank jowl salami. Filet mignon bresaola pork boudin capicola prosciutto. Frankfurter chicken leberkas drumstick ball tip turducken rump spare ribs meatball. Tail salami pork loin ham. Drumstick flank porchetta, hamburger ham swine biltong chicken pancetta. Spare ribs prosciutto t-bone pork belly tenderloin beef ribs. Sirloin bresaola ball tip shank tail porchetta pork boudin filet mignon flank jowl salami. 	<item>
		<title>Services</title>
		<link>http://telelanguage.com/services/</link>
		<pubDate>Thu, 07 Jul 2016 19:16:32 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[admin]]></dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://telelanguage.com/?page_id=1574</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[[vc_row][vc_column width="2/3"][vc_column_text]
<h2>Telephonic Interpretation</h2>
Telelanguage is a leading provider of over-the-phone interpreter services to customers who require fast connections, superior trained and certified interpreters and individually customized rate plans.
<ul>
 	<li>Dedicated 24/7 support</li>
 	<li>Online tutorials, and resources</li>
 	<li>Call reporting &amp; invoicing</li>
 	<li>Rapid deployment</li>
 	<li>Full account transparency</li>
</ul>
<a class="learn-more" href="http://telelanguage.com/services/telephonic-interpretation/" target="_blank">LEARN MORE!</a>
<h2>On-Site Interpretation</h2>
While Over-the-Phone Interpretation offers a fast response when urgent or unexpected language barriers comes up, our On-Site Interpretation Service is a more appropriate solution for appointments planned in advance that may require the extra human interaction and visual contact of interpreter and the Non-English Speaking client.

<a class="learn-more" href="http://telelanguage.com/services/on-site-interpretation/" target="_blank">LEARN MORE!</a>
<h2>Scheduling Software</h2>
Our on-demand Interpreter management platform is specifically designed for a wide variety of industries to better manage their interpretation services.
<ul>
 	<li>Simple to implement, easy to use</li>
 	<li>Executive, interpreter and customer logins</li>
 	<li>Schedule, report and bill all in one system</li>
 	<li>Affordable, yet powerful solution</li>
</ul>
<a class="learn-more" href="http://telelanguage.com/services/scheduling-software/" target="_blank">LEARN MORE!</a>
<h2>Free Translation Tool</h2>
Use Telelanguage online language translator to quickly understand the information you need in real-time. Telelanguage's free online translation service lets you translate any text in the language of your choice. The online translator is quick and easy-to-use!

<a class="learn-more" href="http://telelanguage.com/services/document-translation/" target="_blank">LEARN MORE!</a>[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][vc_column width="1/3"][/vc_column][/vc_row]]]></content:encoded>

	<item>
		<title>On-Site Interpretation</title>
		<link>http://telelanguage.com/services/on-site-interpretation/</link>
		<pubDate>Thu, 07 Jul 2016 19:19:05 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[admin]]></dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://telelanguage.com/?page_id=1580</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[[vc_row el_class="content-rows" css=".vc_custom_1468437868014{margin-bottom: 50px !important;}"][vc_column width="1/4"][vc_column_text]<strong>On-Site Interpretation</strong>

<a href="http://telelanguage.com/faqs/">FAQ’s</a>
<a href="http://telelanguage.com/contact-us/">Request Quote</a>[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][vc_column width="3/4"][vc_column_text]While Over-the-Phone Interpretation offers a fast response when urgent or unexpected language barriers comes up, our On-Site Inter-pretation Service is a more appropriate solution for appointments planned in advance that may require the extra human interaction and visual contact of interpreter and the Non-English Speaking client.

<img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-2699" src="http://telelanguage.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/07/LiveInterpreter.jpg" alt="liveinterpreter" width="602" height="300" />

Our network of medically trained and certified interpreters is available 24/7/365 covering over200 languages. Our interpreters can be on your location in as little as 30 minutes from the time you make your initial request It is essen-tial to communicate effectively in every medi-cal situation with a non-English speaking client. That's why it is so important to choose a company with a proven record of success and expertise in the medical interpretation industry. Telelanguage is that company!
<h3 style="font-weight: bold;">Situations For On-Site Interpretation Services:</h3>
• Lengthy appointments or interviews planned in advance
• Complex, time-consuming issues
• Multiple patient appointments scheduled close to each other
• Where the Limited English Speaker prefers to have the Interpreter on-site
• Where the Limited English Speaker feels uncomfortable using the telephone
• Where hand and body gestures are essential to get a message across
<h3 style="font-weight: bold;">Interpreter Certification</h3>
Telelanguage interpreters is the best professionally trained qualified and certified team in the industry. We have been developing and continuously modifying our interpreter training curriculum since 1991. We have involved leaders from healthcare industry as well as many other industries industries to help us create the most comprehensive medical and community interpreter training and certification programs.[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row el_class="parallax-section forms-rows" css=".vc_custom_1468437688687{background-color: #373d67 !important;}"][vc_column][contact-form-7 id="1554"][/vc_column][/vc_row]]]></content:encoded>

	<item>
		<title>Video Remote Interpretation</title>
		<link>http://telelanguage.com/services/video-remote-interpretation/</link>
		<pubDate>Thu, 07 Jul 2016 19:19:13 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[admin]]></dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://telelanguage.com/?page_id=1581</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[[vc_row el_class="content-rows"][vc_column width="1/4"][vc_column_text]<strong>Video Remote Interpretation:</strong>

<a href="http://telelanguage.com/faqs/">FAQ’s</a>
<a href="http://telelanguage.com/contact-us/">Request Quote</a>[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][vc_column width="3/4"][vc_column_text]Video remote interpreting (VRI) is a video telecommunication service that uses devices such as web cameras or videophones to provide sign language or spoken language interpreting services. This is done through a remote or offsite interpreter, in order to communicate with persons with whom there is a communication barrier. Video Remote Interpreting, or VRI, can be an integral component of any language service plan. Telelanguage offers state-of-the-art VRI technology to round out our language solution package. We use a robust and highly secure business class video connectivity platform that is accessible from any customer office or field site. We make video easier than ever using standard laptop or desktop equipment available at the customers site.  VRI software and other user interfaces are provided at no cost to our customers.

<img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-2695" src="http://telelanguage.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/07/Video-Remote-Interpreting.jpg" alt="language" width="600" height="400" />

VRI can be a perfect solution for a number of industries and applications. From healthcare to legal, business to education, 911 to government, and more, VRI provides a unique opportunity to connect your clients and community. Telelanguage is transforming the interpretation world with video remote interpretation, filling the gap between over-the-phone and on-site interpretation services. Conventional on-site interpreting typically requires at least a two-hour minimum charge and possibly mileage and travel charges. Our VRI service saves your interpretation budget since we do not charge hourly minimums and extra expenses.

It's one thing to interpret words; it's another thing to know that those words were understood.  Our video remote interpretation services make it possible to:
<ul>
 	<li>Visual support with enhanced accuracy for ten (10) most common languages and American Sign Language (ASL)</li>
 	<li>See facial expressions of the interpreter and know they understood what was said</li>
 	<li>Confirm the meaning of non-verbal communication</li>
 	<li>Help the conversation for you, your interpreter and your non-English speaking client</li>
</ul>
VRI promotes the highest level of accuracy in interpretation services, second only to in-person interpretation services. We currently have multiple accounts that are actively using our VRI technology, and would be happy to provide references, or discuss our capabilities.[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row el_class="parallax-section forms-rows" css=".vc_custom_1471019603370{margin-top: 50px !important;background-color: #373d67 !important;}"][vc_column][contact-form-7 id="1554"][/vc_column][/vc_row]]]></content:encoded>

		<title>Scheduling Software</title>
		<link>http://telelanguage.com/services/scheduling-software/</link>
		<pubDate>Thu, 07 Jul 2016 19:19:24 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[admin]]></dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://telelanguage.com/?page_id=1582</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[[vc_row el_class="content-rows" css=".vc_custom_1471038372685{margin-bottom: 50px !important;}"][vc_column width="1/4"][vc_column_text]<strong>Scheduling Software</strong>

<a href="http://telelanguage.com/faqs/">FAQ’s</a>
<a href="http://telelanguage.com/contact-us/">Request Quote</a>[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][vc_column width="3/4"][vc_column_text]
<h3 style="font-weight: bold; text-align: center;">14 Day FREE Trial - Schedule a Demo Today!
Call <a style="color: #767676; text-decoration: none;" href="tel:888.983.5352">888.983.5352</a> For More Info!</h3>
<center>
<img class="size-full wp-image-1724 aligncenter" src="http://telelanguage.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/07/Scheduling-img.png" alt="Scheduling-img" width="530" height="323" /></center>
<h3 style="font-weight: bold;"></h3>
<h3 style="font-weight: bold;"></h3>
<h3 style="font-weight: bold;"></h3>
<h3 style="font-weight: bold;"></h3>
<h3 style="font-weight: bold;"></h3>
<h3 style="font-weight: bold;"></h3>
<h3 style="font-weight: bold;"></h3>
<h3 style="font-weight: bold;"></h3>
<h3 style="font-weight: bold;">Getting Started</h3>
Request a free demo or select the package that best fits your company needs. Your login ID and Password will be emailed to you.
<h3 style="font-weight: bold;">Login Using Your Credentials</h3>
You complete interpreter scheduling software is ready for business. Enter your customers and interpreters into the system or follow instructions to download it using Excel.
<h3 style="font-weight: bold;">Customize It</h3>
Feel free to customize the look and feel of your new Interpreter Scheduling Software to reflect your company colors, logos, forms and messages.
<h3 style="font-weight: bold;">Manage Your Language Services</h3>
You customers can start entering interpreter requests online and interpreters should be managing their schedules and appointments using your company ISS.
<h3 style="font-weight: bold;">Access From Anywhere</h3>
Monitor how interpreter requests are entered and get assigned to interpreters without your staff involvement. Make necessary scheduling adjustments as necessary.
<h3 style="font-weight: bold;">Invoice Customers and Pay Interpreters</h3>
Create invoices to customers and payment logs to interpreters based on the complete history of each assignment, including customer signed order forms.[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row el_class="parallax-section forms-rows" css=".vc_custom_1468481250119{background-color: #373d67 !important;}"][vc_column][contact-form-7 id="1554"][/vc_column][/vc_row]]]></content:encoded>

		<content:encoded><![CDATA[[vc_row el_class="content-rows"][vc_column width="1/4"][vc_column_text]<strong>Telephonic Interpretation</strong>

<a href="http://telelanguage.com/faqs/">FAQ’s</a>
<a href="http://telelanguage.com/contact-us/">Request Quote</a>

<strong>Contact Us Now for a Demonstration</strong>

If you want to take your non-English-speaking customer support to the next level:

<a style="text-decoration: underline;" href="#">Sign up</a> for our telephonic interpretation services or <a style="text-decoration: underline;" href="#">Fill out our quick information request form</a> and one of our customer service representatives will contact you to provide additional information on the advantages of our telephonic interpretation services. Unless you contact us, you will never know what you’ve been missing with your current language vendor.

<strong>Transition Program</strong>

Companies are switching to Telelanguage for a variety of reasons, but no matter what your interpretation need is, you can be assured that your transition to Telelanguage will be seamless and smooth. The Telelanguage Transition Program includes:

• Transition Meeting and Plan
• Data Entry and Analysis
• Access Code Integration (if appropriate)
• Services Infrastructure Customization if needed)
• Interpreter Access Training[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][vc_column width="3/4"][vc_column_text]Are you in desperate need of a more customer-oriented telephonic interpretation vendor? Are you looking for better rates? Are you seeking a customer support and services team that responds to your needs quickly? If you are ready to move the customer support for your non-English speaking clients to the next level, but don’t know where to turn, start by talking to Telelanguage today.

<center>
<iframe style="margin-bottom: 25px; border-bottom: 1px solid #FFF;" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/C5WDHcGoOa8?rel=0" width="560" height="315" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen="allowfullscreen"></iframe></center>Telelanguage is a leading telephonic interpretation provider offering demanding clients effective, reliable, custom solutions; responsive customer support; performance improvement services and superior rates. We also provide incentives and assistance in switching from other providers to Telelanguage.

<strong>Advanced Features</strong>

Telelanguage provides clients the leading-edge technology and professional services they need to offer the best language support. We offer flexible solutions, including:

• Advanced features such as automated interpreter connect
• Customized and language dependent rate plans
• Full-time, dedicated customer support•
• Online and on-location training
• Filter-based qualification interpreter connect
• Detailed customized usage reports and client newsletters
• Performance improvement consulting/service reviews
• Responsive and helpful client services team
• Online tracking system and account management

<strong>Why organizations are switching to Telelanguage:</strong>

<strong>Healthcare Organizations</strong>
Medically trained interpreters, HIPPA compliant services, lower cost

<strong>State and Federal Agencies</strong>
Confidentiality compliance, greater flexibility, responsive support

<strong>Insurance and Legal Services</strong>
Strict confidentiality compliance, interpreters trained in specific terminology,

<strong>Public Utility, Police and 911</strong>
Quick interpreter connect to all languages, flexible rate plans and volume discounts

<strong>Call Centers and Help Desks</strong>
Lower cost, advanced features, improved services delivery and skill-bases interpreter connect features.[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row full_width="stretch_row" el_class="parallax-section forms-rows" css=".vc_custom_1468433986414{margin-top: 50px !important;background-color: #373d67 !important;}"][vc_column][contact-form-7 id="1554"][/vc_column][/vc_row]]]></content:encoded>

	<item>
		<title>Industries</title>
		<link>http://telelanguage.com/industries/</link>
		<pubDate>Thu, 07 Jul 2016 19:21:58 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[admin]]></dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://telelanguage.com/?page_id=1592</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[[vc_row][vc_column width="2/3"][vc_column_text]
<h2>Healthcare</h2>
When you are communicating with non-English speaking patients you need support that you can trust, especially in emergency situations. At Telelanguage, we provide that support with a 24/7 one-point-of-contact account management system. Over 70% of our current client base are healthcare entities.

<a class="learn-more" href="http://telelanguage.com/industries/healthcare/" target="_blank">LEARN MORE!</a>
<h2>Government</h2>
Government clients, whether Federal, State, County, Municipality, or otherwise, present unique challenges and opportunities when it comes to providing Interpretation and Translation services. Telelanguage’s current client base is comprised of over 20% government entities.

<a class="learn-more" href="http://telelanguage.com/industries/government/" target="_blank">LEARN MORE!</a>
<h2>Social Services</h2>
Social services, whether public or private sector, provide essential services aimed at promoting the welfare of others. This critical industry tends to have a higher rate of interpretation and translation needs, an industry Telelanguage has been providing services to for over 25 years.

<a class="learn-more" href="http://telelanguage.com/industries/social-services/" target="_blank">LEARN MORE!</a>
<h2>Financial Services</h2>
Financial services are economic services provided by the finance industry, which encompasses a broad range of businesses.As the economic world grows smaller, and global business grows larger, different cultures and languages are intersecting at an ever-increasing pace. Telelanguage, with over 25 years providing support to financial institutions, believes security, compliance and customer satisfaction to be the three of the most crucial aspects of the Finance industry.

<a class="learn-more" href="http://telelanguage.com/industries/financial-services/" target="_blank">LEARN MORE!</a>
<h2>Insurance</h2>
The Insurance industry is constantly faced with unique challenges. From managing risk and regulatory complexity, to ever evolving business models, to market segment obstacles, Insurance providers must be ever diligent. In addition to these challenges, customer satisfaction, quality control and security are also high on the list of important focuses.

<a class="learn-more" href="http://telelanguage.com/industries/insurance/" target="_blank">LEARN MORE!</a>
<h2>Utilities</h2>
The Utility industry faces a number of challenges in today’s market. From cyberattacks to customer expectations, energy storage to smarter, greener energy, the Utility industry is constantly evolving. After remaining relatively unchanged for the past century, the grid is confronted by a series of new challenges that are forcing an evolution of business models, while changing user expectations and causing regulatory models to adapt.

<a class="learn-more" href="http://telelanguage.com/industries/utilities/" target="_blank">LEARN MORE!</a>
<h2>911 Emergency Services</h2>
Telelanguage is the only language service provider that will provide you with certified 911, U.S.-based interpreters available 24/7/365 – at the most competitive rates. Our 25+ years of experience supporting emergency call centers will give you 100% reliability along with a dedicated account support team.

<a class="learn-more" href="http://telelanguage.com/industries/911-emergency-services/" target="_blank">LEARN MORE!</a>
<h2>Legal and Judicial</h2>
Telelanguage has over 25 years of providing the Legal and Judicial industry with language services. We understand the unique challenges facing the Legal system, and have a vast network of active clients and success stories to show for it. We understand that community image is very important, as well as compliance, security and regulations.

<a class="learn-more" href="http://telelanguage.com/industries/legal-and-judicial/" target="_blank">LEARN MORE!</a>
<h2>Travel/Hospitality</h2>
The Travel and Hospitality industry is constantly having to balance excellent customer service, with the highest levels of quality. Challenges facing the Hospitality industry include sustainable development, operating issues and the increasing demand for faster, more user-friendly technology applications.

<a class="learn-more" href="http://telelanguage.com/industries/travelhospitality/" target="_blank">LEARN MORE!</a>
<h2>Telecommunications</h2>
The Telecommunications industry bridges the gap between the customer experience, quality and technology. Telecommunication providers face a number of challenges in today’s market such as building and maintaining the right infrastructure, controlling costs, building a brand, monetizing new services, and prioritizing data.

<a class="learn-more" href="http://telelanguage.com/industries/telecommunications/" target="_blank">LEARN MORE!</a>[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][vc_column width="1/3"][/vc_column][/vc_row]]]></content:encoded>

	<item>
		<title>Optional Equipment</title>
		<link>http://telelanguage.com/resources/optional-equipment/</link>
		<pubDate>Thu, 07 Jul 2016 19:20:58 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[admin]]></dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://telelanguage.com/?page_id=1595</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[[vc_row][vc_column][vc_column_text]As part of Telelanguage’s language service solution, additional equipment can also be included. As an option for our clients, we offer dual handset phones, phone splitters and cordless phones. Our standard dual handset phone, the Med-Pat D2200, is a deluxe Euro-Style, 2 Handset Telephone, specifically designed for interpretation. Other features of this phone include:
<ul>
 	<li>MicroBlock<sup>TM</sup> Protection (Antibacterial Surface Protection)</li>
 	<li>Patented Volume Plus Button designed with features for the hearing impaired aiding 70% of elderly patients with high-frequency hearing loss (the Boost Button increases volume range to 27.5db)</li>
 	<li>Built in CLEARING AID® circuitry automatically adjusts frequency response for improved clarity. This is an aid to 70% of Patients with high-frequency hearing loss.</li>
 	<li>Designed with twin handsets the 2 Can Talk ™ telephone ensures privacy during conference calls, in-house interpreting, or while using a language interpretation service. Each user has a separate handset for confidential communication.</li>
 	<li>Easy to wipe down, sleek profile, Lite Touch Keypad with Day Glow No Wear / Non Rub Off keys</li>
 	<li>Free Faceplate Customization (Telelanguage provides customized nameplates as part of our package – including your dedicated toll free number, and any other information you’d like to include)</li>
 	<li>Rotary Handset Volume Control plus additional Volume Plus Button on Base</li>
 	<li>Built in speakerphone with automatic differential balancing; &gt;80 dB receive to transmit.</li>
 	<li>Three Memory Buttons with Non-Volatile Permanent Memory. No Battery Needed.</li>
 	<li>Two Headset Connections with Separate Volume Controls.</li>
</ul>
In addition to our client-facing equipment, our internal equipment and software includes 16 servers stored in a Tier III professional-grade data center, complete Adobe and Microsoft suites, and multiple interpretation and translation management systems. Our goal is to make the entire interpretation and translation service experience as seamless, efficient, and user-friendly as possible. Our technology, software, and equipment offerings assist in achieving these goals.[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][/vc_row]]]></content:encoded>

	<item>
		<title>Interpreter Certification</title>
		<link>http://telelanguage.com/resources/interpreter-certification/</link>
		<pubDate>Thu, 07 Jul 2016 19:21:05 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[admin]]></dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://telelanguage.com/?page_id=1596</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[[vc_row css=".vc_custom_1469040567429{margin-bottom: 50px !important;}"][vc_column][vc_column_text]The Telelanguage Interpreter Certification Program, or TICP, is a national certification program for Over-the-Phone and Face-to-Face interpreting. TICP training targets all industries, including healthcare, education, government, law enforcement, 9-1-1 call centers, financial institutions, business/commercial, and social community services.

The TICP course covers ethics, interpreter roles, basic skills (from pre-session to post-session), positioning and terminology, modes of interpreting, steps for sight translation, cultural mediation, and other vital skills. The program also offers an overview of the profession, and discusses the importance of interpreter certification.

<img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-2707" src="http://telelanguage.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/07/INTCertification-1.jpg" alt="intcertification" width="800" height="383" />

TICP goes on to incorporate skill building drills, role play, small group work, video segments, vignettes, group discussion, and case study review.TICP is a dynamic, interactive program, which builds on over 25 years of Telelanguage experience. Currently, the industry standard is a 30-hour training course for certification. TICP utilizes a 120-hour training course, coupled with a 370-page training manual, for a highly comprehensive learning experience - exceeding industry standards.

TICP includes information and training on:
<ul>
 	<li>National ethics and standards of practice for interpreters</li>
 	<li>Basic skills: pre-session preparation, introductions positioning, register, tone, halting the session, note-taking, memory skills, closing the session</li>
 	<li>Legal obligations of interpreters (Title VI, impartiality, reporting abuse, disclosing conflicts of interest, etc.)</li>
 	<li>Interpreter roles: interpreting and mediation (in and outside the session)</li>
 	<li>Setting boundaries: interpreter neutrality and ethical decision-making</li>
 	<li>Culture and cultural mediation: cultural competence; cultural practices; bias and discrimination; educating clients and colleagues about culture and interpreting</li>
 	<li>Information on community systems (K-12 schools and U.S. education; human and social services; U.S. health care)</li>
 	<li>Expert guidance on how to adapt interpreter ethics and standards to a bilingual employee’s workplace: addressing conflicts with supervisors; how workplace and interpreter ethics may collide; advocacy; promoting equal access to services; what interpreters should never translate (and why); insurance and liability</li>
</ul>
In addition to TICP training, Telelanguage also provides medical certification for our interpreters. We require 120 Hours of Academic Medical Training &amp; Healthcare Interpreting Ethics, which is well above the National Board of Medical Interpreters Requirements. Because of the growing number of LEP patients, the need for healthcare interpreters has grown swiftly in the last decade.

When a patient has limited English skills, it is nearly impossible for even the most skilled clinician to provide high-quality healthcare services without the assistance of accurate interpreting performed by a trained, qualified interpreter who is versed in medical terminology. Healthcare Interpreters often have to educate other members of the healthcare team across the disciplines regarding the duties, requirements, and ethical standards involved in healthcare interpreting.

Throughout the U.S., Interpreters are becoming key and highly valued members of the healthcare team. Their responsibilities have evolved greatly in the last decade, and this trend is continuing.[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row el_class="parallax-section forms-rows" css=".vc_custom_1469040548076{background-color: #373d67 !important;}"][vc_column][contact-form-7 id="1554"][/vc_column][/vc_row]]]></content:encoded>
		<excerpt:encoded><![CDATA[]]></excerpt:encoded>

	<item>
		<title>Healthcare</title>
		<link>http://telelanguage.com/industries/healthcare/</link>
		<pubDate>Thu, 07 Jul 2016 19:22:33 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[admin]]></dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://telelanguage.com/?page_id=1604</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[[vc_row][vc_column width="2/3"][vc_column_text]When you are communicating with non-English speaking patients you need support that you can trust, especially in emergency situations. At Telelanguage, we provide that support with a 24/7 one-point-of-contact account management system. Over 70% of our current client base are healthcare entities.

<img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-2710" src="http://telelanguage.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/07/Healthcare.jpg" alt="healthcare" width="600" height="314" />

While improving your language support services we will find ways to reduce your interpretation cost and increase overall patient satisfaction. We DON’T leave you on HOLD. When we say we are faster, we’re talking about more than just answering your calls. We pride ourselves on interpreter connect times that are setting industry standards.

We tailor our service to your exact requirements. No matter what language your patients speak, we connect you with US-based medically certified interpreters FASTER than any other vendor.

We are committed to providing the best medically trained interpreters in the emergency healthcare industry. In pursuit of this goal the Interpreter Certification Center (ICC) was established to provide quality training &amp; education for interpreters.

Free Cultural Awareness training is available to our healthcare customers to know how to work with Limited English Proficiency (LEP) patients. Both training and support emphasis help create an environment of acceptance and nurturing in any clinic or hospital where multiple cultures interact. It helps doctors and nurses to work respectfully and effectively with other employees and patients of culturally diverse traditions, dress, and language.

Telelanguage defines and establishes educational requirements and qualifications for medical interpreters and professional standards of practice.

One low per-minute rate includes paper and/or electronic invoicing, one second increment billing, no monthly minimums, free third party dialing with NO HIDDEN FEES of any kind.

We offer Free Service Trial Programs where you can test our services before entering into an agreement.

Our Call Volume Discount Plans are considered to be the best in the industry and are only available to our Healthcare clients. Our contract renewal policy guarantees no rate increases. All interpreter reference materials such as language posters, dialing instructions, tips on effective communication with LEP including dual handset phones are all provided for Free.[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][vc_column width="1/3"][vc_widget_sidebar title="Other Industries" sidebar_id="shop"][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row el_class="parallax-section forms-rows" css=".vc_custom_1470341138839{margin-top: 50px !important;background-color: #373d67 !important;}"][vc_column][contact-form-7 id="1554"][/vc_column][/vc_row]]]></content:encoded>

	<item>
		<title>Government</title>
		<link>http://telelanguage.com/industries/government/</link>
		<pubDate>Thu, 07 Jul 2016 19:23:32 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[admin]]></dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://telelanguage.com/?page_id=1605</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[[vc_row][vc_column width="2/3"][vc_column_text]Government clients, whether Federal, State, County, Municipality, or otherwise, present unique challenges and opportunities when it comes to providing Interpretation and Translation services. Telelanguage’s current client base is comprised of over 20% government entities. Telelanguage’s capabilities include translation of written, electronic and multi-media material to and from English and native Foreign languages, as well as Interpretation of oral communication to and from English and native Foreign Languages. Translation capabilities include but are not limited to: Business, Legal, Medical, Technical, Documents, Braille, Software, Website localization for Internet and Intranet, Video subtitling, captioning, and Transcriptions for Title III Monitoring and more. While Interpretation includes but is not limited to: Simultaneous, Consecutive, Escort, Community, Telephonic and Voiceovers. Interpreter forums may include meetings, conferences, seminars, litigation, briefings, training and more.

Telelanguage offers comprehensive Language Services in support of local, national, or global requirements that support the missions of military, law enforcement, homeland and national security organizations among others. Services include but are not limited to: Collecting, translating/interpreting and delivering mission related data; performing data analysis; cultural consulting; role-playing; Title III monitoring and intercepts and more.

Telelanguage is aware of the confidential, yet culturally sensitive nature of government. We’ve been an expert in both for over 25 years. Keeping customer information secure and confidential is a priority for Telelanguage, Inc. We are providing this privacy notice to our customers who utilize our telephonic and face-to-face interpretation services. We hope this helps you understand how we handle the personal and other confidential information about you and your non-English speaking clients that our interpreters encounter during the interpretation process. In addition, our extensive certification and training programs focus on cultural sensitivity to include topics such as cultural mediation, cultural competence, cultural practices, bias and discrimination, and educating clients and colleagues about culture and interpreting.

We understand the needs of government. At Telelanguage, we balance the highest levels of customer service, with competitive rates, the latest technology and the most secure data and interpretation standards in the industry. If it’s important to government, it’s important to Telelanguage.

	<item>
		<title>Financial Services</title>
		<link>http://telelanguage.com/industries/financial-services/</link>
		<pubDate>Thu, 07 Jul 2016 19:23:51 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[admin]]></dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://telelanguage.com/?page_id=1606</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[[vc_row][vc_column width="2/3"][vc_column_text]Financial services are economic services provided by the finance industry, which encompasses a broad range of businesses. As the economic world grows smaller, and global business grows larger, different cultures and languages are intersecting at an ever-increasing pace. Telelanguage, with over 25 years providing support to financial institutions, believes security, compliance and customer satisfaction to be the three of the most crucial aspects of the Finance industry.

Financial Services is a highly specialized industry, one with very little room for error. At Telelanguage, we take Quality Assurance very seriously. Our internal control processes and Quality Assurance commitment is highly successful and fully operational. Our goal is 100% on time connection record, and 100% customer satisfaction. Telelanguage expects our clients to have a quality interpretation experience for each and every interaction. Our interpreters act as a bridge between our clients and their limited English proficient (LEP) customer, therefore client and customer can focus on the business at hand, rather than the interpretation experience. That is why we put so much industry research, thought, and effort into each detail of what we do and how we do it. Our quality program processes and other Internal Control Procedures were developed to address each segment of an interpretation request. These segments include: 1) Answer Time and Critical Data Collection, 2) Call Center Customer Service &amp; Connection Times, 3) Interpreter Greeting and Performance, 4) Interpreter Code of Ethics, Cultural Sensitivity in Meeting Customer Mission Critical Needs; and Professional Call Closeout, 5) Conflict Resolution, and 6) Billing and Reporting.

In addition to our intensive Quality Assurance plans, Telelanguage enforces a strict infrastructure of training and certification for all of our interpreters and translators. These rigorous requirements promote the highest levels of professionalism and confidentiality - a level even the most secure financial institutions are confident with. Also, all of our data is stored in a Tier III professional-grade data center. Regardless of the scenario, your interpretation and translation services will remain unaffected. If it’s important to you, it’s important to us.[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][vc_column width="1/3"][vc_widget_sidebar title="Other Industries" sidebar_id="shop"][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row css=".vc_custom_1470340936782{margin-top: 50px !important;background-color: #373d67 !important;}" el_class="parallax-section forms-rows"][vc_column][contact-form-7 id="1554"][/vc_column][/vc_row]]]></content:encoded>

	<item>
		<title>Insurance</title>
		<link>http://telelanguage.com/industries/insurance/</link>
		<pubDate>Thu, 07 Jul 2016 19:23:59 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[admin]]></dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://telelanguage.com/?page_id=1607</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[[vc_row][vc_column width="2/3"][vc_column_text]The Insurance industry is constantly faced with unique challenges. From managing risk and regulatory complexity, to ever evolving business models, to market segment obstacles, Insurance providers must be ever diligent. In addition to these challenges, customer satisfaction, quality control and security are also high on the list of important focuses. Across the country, and the world, Insurance providers often deal with clients at some of their most stressful, and critical times. As a language service provider with over 25 years in business, Telelanguage understands the keys to communicating with any demographic, culture or language – especially in these demanding scenarios.

As the world economy becomes increasingly connected, technology and bridging cultural gaps become more important. The team at Telelanguage includes a network of over 4,000 interpreters and translators, with experience in over 240 languages. Our services are available around the clock, 24/7/365. Our telephonic technology allows for connect times of 7-10 seconds – well below the industry average, while Face-to-Face interpreters can sometimes be on-site in under 30 minutes. In a world that is ever evolving, Telelanguage continues to develop its own proprietary technology to account for any surges or volumes that the Insurance industry may face.Based on 25 years of providing interpretation services we confirm the 99% appointment fulfillment rate, lower than competition interpreter tardiness, higher client level of satisfaction and higher cost savings to our customers. We dispatch certified interpreters to hundreds of locations throughout each day, across the country.  Our language interpreters are matched to each assignment on the basis of their interpreting skills, industry knowledge, experience and geographical location. We have a rigorous selection and certification program to ensure that all our interpreters are qualified to serve our customers.

Telelanguage is committed to serving the Insurance industry, just as our Insurance clients are committed to serving their customers. We guarantee that our combination of excellent customer service, forward-thinking technology, competitive pricing and disciplined quality assurance approach meet to provide the Insurance industry with an ideal language service solution.

	<item>
		<title>Utilities</title>
		<link>http://telelanguage.com/industries/utilities/</link>
		<pubDate>Thu, 07 Jul 2016 19:24:07 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[admin]]></dc:creator>

		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[[vc_row][vc_column width="2/3"][vc_column_text]The Utility industry faces a number of challenges in today’s market. From cyberattacks to customer expectations, energy storage to smarter, greener energy, the Utility industry is constantly evolving. After remaining relatively unchanged for the past century, the grid is confronted by a series of new challenges that are forcing an evolution of business models, while changing user expectations and causing regulatory models to adapt. As an expert in exceeding customer expectations, Telelanguage is able to provide a solution to a niche challenge: interpretation and translation.

As the Utility industry faces these new challenges, the team at Telelanguage stands by to provide interpretation and translation services at the highest customer service levels, while balancing competitive pricing and cutting edge technology. In addition, our interpretation and translation services are hosted over a secure, proprietary platform that our clients can customize and access 24/7.

Our values are centered around customer service, professionalism, maintaining confidentiality, and retaining the best interpreters and translators through rigorous training and certification. By selecting Telelanguage, you will effectively mitigate all costs and technical performance risk with Interpretation and Translation Services performed at the highest industry standards, improve customer satisfaction, increase services utilization, improved customer-support, and maintain a community friendly image.

In addition to remaining compliant with all government, privacy and security regulations, Telelanguage is able to implement any new contract typically within 24 hours. There is virtually zero transition impact for a new client. If you’ve selected Telelanguage to provide your interpretation and translation services, we ensure that the implementation process with be as quick and seamless as possible. All training, both initial and ongoing, will be provided at no charge, in addition to any marketing or training collateral.

The simple definition of a public utility is to provide a public service. As a language service provider for over 25 years, Telelanguage knows first-hand how important delivering on a public service can be.[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][vc_column width="1/3"][vc_widget_sidebar title="Other Industries" sidebar_id="shop"][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row el_class="parallax-section forms-rows" css=".vc_custom_1470422831046{margin-top: 50px !important;background-color: #373d67 !important;}"][vc_column][contact-form-7 id="1554"][/vc_column][/vc_row]]]></content:encoded>

	<item>
		<title>Social Services</title>
		<link>http://telelanguage.com/industries/social-services/</link>
		<pubDate>Thu, 07 Jul 2016 19:23:40 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[admin]]></dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://telelanguage.com/?page_id=1610</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[[vc_row][vc_column width="2/3"][vc_column_text]Social services, whether public or private sector, provide essential services aimed at promoting the welfare of others. This critical industry tends to have a higher rate of interpretation and translation needs, an industry Telelanguage has been providing services to for over 25 years.

Telelanguage provides services that combine meeting mission-critical agency needs with a high quality, best value approach.  With over 25 years of language services experience and a comprehensive Quality Assurance Plan to accurately track, monitor and control all-operations, we can effectively mitigate all cost and technical performance risk to the Social Services industry at the highest industry standards.

We understand that Social Services must always be “on.” Therefore, Telelanguage has Surge Management plans to handle any capacity of interpretation or translation needs. We are Federal Government compliant with FEMA, Homeland Security, natural disaster and border contingencies, as well as having military mobilization Business Continuity Plans in place to support the emergency needs of your residents. Telelanguage possesses the proven staff and capacity to support mass casualty and mass effect incidents that will not affect our ability to execute services to non-English speakers.  We possess the domestic security and medical surge capacity for emergency management services deployment of interpreters and translators consistent with Department of Homeland Security goals and initiatives.

&nbsp;

In addition, we have the proven capacity and ability to evaluate and care for a markedly increased volume of patients with both on-site and telephonic Medical Certified interpreters in simultaneous multiple locations.  We’re able to accommodate unforeseen events that may challenge or exceed normal operating capacity. Telelanguage shall easily integrate into any customer work environment.  Surge requirements span the range of specialized medical and health services that are not normally available at the location where they are needed, such as pediatric care provided at non-pediatric facilities or burn care services at a non-burn centers.

&nbsp;

Just as Social Services are aimed at providing services for the benefit of the community, Telelanguage’s primary goal is to support Social Services in the provided solutions.[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][vc_column width="1/3"][vc_widget_sidebar title="Other Industries" sidebar_id="shop"][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row el_class="parallax-section forms-rows" css=".vc_custom_1470341194091{margin-top: 50px !important;background-color: #373d67 !important;}"][vc_column][contact-form-7 id="1554"][/vc_column][/vc_row]]]></content:encoded>

	<item>
		<title>911 Emergency Services</title>
		<link>http://telelanguage.com/industries/911-emergency-services/</link>
		<pubDate>Thu, 07 Jul 2016 19:24:34 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[admin]]></dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://telelanguage.com/?page_id=1616</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[[vc_row][vc_column width="2/3"][vc_column_text]Telelanguage is the only language service provider that will provide you with certified 911, U.S.-based interpreters available 24/7/365 - at the most competitive rates. Our 25+ years of experience supporting emergency call centers will give you 100% reliability along with a dedicated account support team.

Telelanguage guarantees the highest quality of services, while providing the best value to our clients, and increasing overall client satisfaction.We DON’T leave you on HOLD. We maintain the fastest times in the industry through both call answer time, as well as interpreter connect times. We’re proud to say that our connection times are setting industry standards.No matter what language your callers speak, we connect you with U.S.-based professionally certified interpreters FASTER than any other vendor. We understand, especially in emergency services, that seconds matter.

In addition to being the fastest, we are also committed to providing the best trained interpreters in the emergency industry. In pursuit of this goal the Interpreter Certification Center (ICC) was established to provide quality training &amp; education for emergency interpreters.

Aside from the ICC, Telelanguage also maintains multiple other certification requirements for medical and legal situations. Free Cultural Awareness training is also available to our customers to better understand how to work with LEP clients.

Both training and experience help create an environment of acceptance and urgency in any emergency situation where multiple cultures interact. Our training helps 911 dispatch and other staff to work respectfully and effectively with other employees and LEP’s.Our low ratesincludes paper and/or electronic invoicing, one-second increment billing, no monthly minimums, free third party dialing and NO HIDDEN FEES of any kind.We offer Free Service Trial Programs allowing you to test our services before entering into an agreement.

Our Call Volume Discount Plans are considered to be the best in the industry, and are only available to our Emergency/911 clients. Our contract renewal policy guarantees no rate increases. All interpreter reference materials such as language posters, dialing instructions, and tips on effective communication with LEP are all provided at no cost.[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][vc_column width="1/3"][vc_widget_sidebar title="Other Industries" sidebar_id="shop"][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row el_class="parallax-section forms-rows" css=".vc_custom_1470423021726{margin-top: 50px !important;background-color: #373d67 !important;}"][vc_column][contact-form-7 id="1554"][/vc_column][/vc_row]]]></content:encoded>

		<title>Legal and Judicial</title>
		<link>http://telelanguage.com/industries/legal-and-judicial/</link>
		<pubDate>Thu, 07 Jul 2016 19:24:42 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[admin]]></dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://telelanguage.com/?page_id=1617</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[[vc_row][vc_column width="2/3"][vc_column_text]Telelanguage has over 25 years of providing the Legal and Judicial industry with language services. We understand the unique challenges facing the Legal system, and have a vast network of active clients and success stories to show for it. We understand that community image is very important, as well as compliance, security and regulations. We fully understand your linguistics support needs and challenges you face. With contracts currently in place with legal systems across the country, we have a proven history of success working with similar target populations. As the Legal and Judicial industries continue to evolve, so does the technology that Telelanguage is able to provide. Our interpreter platform is proprietary technology, with the ability to be customized to every client.

Keeping customer information secure and confidential is a priority for Telelanguage, Inc. We provide a privacy notice to our customers who utilize our telephonic and face-to-face interpretation services. We protect personal and confidential information encountered during the interpretation process by maintaining physical, electronic, and procedural safeguards that meet or exceed applicable law. All employees and interpreters who have access to personal information must agree to follow appropriate standards of security and confidentiality. We train our employee and interpreters on how to properly handle personal and confidential information and we restrict access to that information. Telelanguage does not collect or use customer confidential information without consent from all parties.

Telelanguage ensures its network of interpreters and translators are trained and certified using the most rigorous criteria. Modules include sections on legal proceedings and human services. Telelanguage has developed a level of institutional knowledge and streamlined processes that allow us to provide our clients worry-free service.All Telelanguage employees and field contractor assets carry one or multiple linguistic or translation certifications; degrees or advanced degrees; background and criminal history checks; or other industry certification and background experience validation or verifications in medical, financial, courts, corrections and other fields. Criminal history, background investigations and Non-Disclosure Agreements (NDA) are in place with all staff and contractor staff to support a diverse range of customer needs before they are assigned to support our clientele.[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][vc_column width="1/3"][vc_widget_sidebar title="Other Industries" sidebar_id="shop"][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row el_class="parallax-section forms-rows" css=".vc_custom_1470423026594{margin-top: 50px !important;background-color: #373d67 !important;}"][vc_column][contact-form-7 id="1554"][/vc_column][/vc_row]]]></content:encoded>

	<item>
		<title>Travel/Hospitality</title>
		<link>http://telelanguage.com/industries/travel-hospitality/</link>
		<pubDate>Thu, 07 Jul 2016 19:24:49 +0000</pubDate>

		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[[vc_row][vc_column width="2/3"][vc_column_text]The Travel and Hospitality industry is constantly having to balance excellent customer service, with the highest levels of quality. Challenges facing the Hospitality industry include sustainable development, operating issues and the increasing demand for faster, more user-friendly technology applications. As a language service provider, with over 25 years of experience in the Travel and Hospitality field, Telelanguage will work tirelessly to bring your services to a virtually endless queue of customers and consumers.

Travel and Hospitality are unique in that this industry is extremely customer-facing. Every day Travel and Hospitality move, house, comfort and connect people from every culture imaginable. The newest trends and topics surrounding hospitality research and development is the management of multicultural talent and the political landscape affecting the hospitality industry. With the development of globalization, multicultural issues are facing and disrupting the industry operators.Bringing the far corners of the world together is part and parcel of what the hospitality sector does. Blending amenities to cater for the needs of the world’s different cultures is central to success for large, international hospitality chains. Cultural issues have never before been such a crucial determinant of how a large hospitality should operate.

Telelanguage prides itself in only networking with interpreters and translators of the highest caliber. Our interpreters must pass rigorous certification and training courses, with a focus on cultural sensitivity. In addition, quality assurance is listed very high in our commitment to our Travel and Hospitality clients. Telelanguage expects our clients to have a high quality interpretation experience. Our interpreters act as a bridge between our clients and their limited English proficient (LEP) customer; therefore, client and customer can focus on the business at hand, rather than the interpretation experience. That is why we put so much industry research, thought, and effort into each detail of what we do and how we do it.[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][vc_column width="1/3"][vc_widget_sidebar title="Other Industries" sidebar_id="shop"][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row el_class="parallax-section forms-rows" css=".vc_custom_1470675224463{margin-top: 50px !important;background-color: #373d67 !important;}"][vc_column][contact-form-7 id="1554"][/vc_column][/vc_row]]]></content:encoded>

	<item>
		<title>Telecommunications</title>
		<link>http://telelanguage.com/industries/telecommunications/</link>
		<pubDate>Thu, 07 Jul 2016 19:24:57 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[admin]]></dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://telelanguage.com/?page_id=1619</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[[vc_row][vc_column width="2/3"][vc_column_text]The Telecommunications industry bridges the gap between the customer experience, quality and technology. Telecommunication providers face a number of challenges in today’s market such as building and maintaining the right infrastructure, controlling costs, building a brand, monetizing new services, and prioritizing data. It’s safe to say that Telecommunications impacts all of us on a daily basis. As the Telecommunication industry grows, the world appears to shrink. For this very reason, Telelanguage has been providing interpretation and translation services since 1991.

With over 4,000 interpreters specializing in over 240 languages, Telelanguage is able to support the Telecommunication industry’s capacity to grow and evolve in an ever competitive market. Our intersection of competitive pricing, forward-thinking technology, quality assurance and customer service create an ideal solution for all of your interpretation and translation requirements.

With all the new service rollouts happening and changes taking place, Telecommunication operators must be sure to control the costs of the current solutions so they can invest in what’s coming next. Developing scalable services now can help manage future costs, since operators will be able to react rapidly to market changes. Telelanguage is able to help you achieve these goals, while maintaining the bottom line.

In addition to cost, maintaining compliance and keeping data safe are also important to our Telecommunication clients. Telelanguage is constantly staying evaluating market trends, recertifying our interpreters and translators, promoting continued education, and emphasizing privacy, confidentiality and professionalism. All of our data is stored in a Tier III, professional grade data center, and quality assurance is of the highest priority. As a company, Telelanguage is consistently monitoring and evaluating our interpreters, translators, technology, billing and reporting practices.  We’re confident that our commitment to excellence will enhance your customer satisfaction, effectively mitigate all costs and technical performance risk with Interpretation and Translation Services, increase service utilization, improve customer-support, all while promoting a community friendly image.[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][vc_column width="1/3"][vc_widget_sidebar title="Other Industries" sidebar_id="shop"][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row el_class="parallax-section forms-rows" css=".vc_custom_1470675254225{margin-top: 50px !important;background-color: #373d67 !important;}"][vc_column][contact-form-7 id="1554"][/vc_column][/vc_row]]]></content:encoded>

	<item>
		<title>Amharic</title>
		<link>http://telelanguage.com/resources/languages-we-provide/amharic/</link>
		<pubDate>Wed, 20 Jul 2016 19:21:33 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[admin]]></dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://telelanguage.com/?page_id=1811</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[[vc_row css=".vc_custom_1469040567429{margin-bottom: 50px !important;}"][vc_column][vc_column_text]Amharic is a Semitic language spoken in North Central Ethiopia. It is the second most spoken Semitic language in the world, after Arabic. It is the "official working" language of the Federal Democratic Republic of Ethiopia and thus has official status nationwide. It is also the official or working language of several of the states within the federal system, including Amhara and the multi-ethnic Southern Nations, Nationalities and Peoples region. It has been the working language of government, the military, and of the Ethiopian Orthodox Church throughout modern times. Outside Ethiopia, Amharic is the language of some 2.7 million emigrants (notably in Egypt, Israel and Sweden), and is spoken in Eritrea by educated Eritreans of the preindependence generation and younger deportees from Ethiopia.[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row el_class="parallax-section forms-rows" css=".vc_custom_1469040548076{background-color: #373d67 !important;}"][vc_column][contact-form-7 id="1554"][/vc_column][/vc_row]]]></content:encoded>
		<excerpt:encoded><![CDATA[]]></excerpt:encoded>

		<title>Arabic</title>
		<link>http://telelanguage.com/resources/languages-we-provide/arabic/</link>
		<pubDate>Wed, 20 Jul 2016 19:43:34 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[admin]]></dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://telelanguage.com/?page_id=1822</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[[vc_row css=".vc_custom_1469040567429{margin-bottom: 50px !important;}"][vc_column][vc_column_text]The Arabic language, or simply Arabic, is the largest member of the Semitic branch of the Afro-Asiatic language family (classification: South Central Semitic) and is closely related to Hebrew and Aramaic. It is spoken throughout the Arab world and is widely studied and known throughout the Islamic world. Arabic has been a literary language since at least the 6th century and is the liturgical language of Islam.[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row el_class="parallax-section forms-rows" css=".vc_custom_1469040548076{background-color: #373d67 !important;}"][vc_column][contact-form-7 id="1554"][/vc_column][/vc_row]]]></content:encoded>

	<item>
		<title>Aramaic</title>
		<link>http://telelanguage.com/resources/languages-we-provide/aramaic/</link>
		<pubDate>Wed, 20 Jul 2016 19:43:55 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[admin]]></dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://telelanguage.com/?page_id=1824</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[[vc_row css=".vc_custom_1469040567429{margin-bottom: 50px !important;}"][vc_column][vc_column_text]Aramaic is a collective term used to describe several Hebrew-influenced Aramaic and Neo-Aramaic languages. Aramaic, like Hebrew, is a Northwest Semitic language, and the two share many features. From the seventh century BCE, Aramaic became the lingua franca of the Middle East. It became the language of diplomacy and trade, but was not used by the Hebrew populace at this early date. As described in 2 Kings 18:26, Hezekiah, king of Judah, negotiates with Assyrian ambassadors in Aramaic rather than Hebrew so that the common people would not understand. During the sixth century BCE, the Babylonian captivity brought the working language of Mesopotamia much more into their daily life of ordinary Jews. Around 500 BCE, Darius I of Persia proclaimed that Aramaic would be the official language for the western half of his empire, and the Eastern Aramaic dialect of Babylon became the official standard.[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row el_class="parallax-section forms-rows" css=".vc_custom_1469040548076{background-color: #373d67 !important;}"][vc_column][contact-form-7 id="1554"][/vc_column][/vc_row]]]></content:encoded>
		<excerpt:encoded><![CDATA[]]></excerpt:encoded>
		<wp:post_id>1824</wp:post_id>
		<wp:post_date><![CDATA[2016-07-20 19:43:55]]></wp:post_date>
		<wp:post_date_gmt><![CDATA[2016-07-20 19:43:55]]></wp:post_date_gmt>
		<wp:comment_status><![CDATA[closed]]></wp:comment_status>

		<content:encoded><![CDATA[[vc_row css=".vc_custom_1469040567429{margin-bottom: 50px !important;}"][vc_column][vc_column_text]Armenian is an Indo-European language spoken by the Armenian people in the Armenian Republic and also used by the Armenian Diaspora. It constitutes an independent branch of the Indo-European language family, though many Indo-Europeanists believe it forms a subgroup with the Greek and Indo-Iranian families (see Clackson 1994 for extensive discussion).[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row el_class="parallax-section forms-rows" css=".vc_custom_1469040548076{background-color: #373d67 !important;}"][vc_column][contact-form-7 id="1554"][/vc_column][/vc_row]]]></content:encoded>
