	<item>
		<title>3 Factors Informing Language Services in the U.S. (Infographic)</title>
		<link>http://telelanguage.com/factors-informing-language-services-infographic/</link>
		<pubDate>Fri, 27 Jan 2017 19:58:17 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[kimberlyscamman]]></dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://telelanguage.com/?p=3199</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<span style="font-weight: 400;">Diversity in our country is at the heart of America. As populations continue to shift, and we become more diverse, the need for effective language services increases in all industries across the United States and qualified interpreters and translators are high-value members in serving the needs of language diverse populations.</span>


<span style="font-weight: 400;">The growing need for language services and </span><a href="http://telelanguage.com/video-remote-interpreting-infographic/"><span style="font-weight: 400;">new technologies like Video Remote Interpreting</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;"> is shaped by many population and demographic trends. Becoming aware of these trends and factors will to provide the best quality language services that fit the needs of today’s diverse populations. </span>

&nbsp;
<h3>Three factors currently informing language services in the United States</h3>

<b>Foreign-born Populations</b>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">Over the past 50 years, 59 Million immigrants have come to the United States, driving population growth and change. About 14% of the total U.S. population is foreign-born. Immigration trends highlight the need for effective language interpretation solutions across the U.S. <a href="http://www.pewhispanic.org/2015/09/28/chapter-5-u-s-foreign-born-population-trends/" target="_blank">Pew Research</a></span>

&nbsp;

<b>Language Diversity and Limited English Proficiency</b>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">The <a href="http://www.census.gov/newsroom/press-releases/2015/cb15-185.html" target="_blank">United States Census Bureau</a> reports at least 350 languages spoken in U.S. homes and over 25 million people were considered to have Limited English Proficiency. Language access programs serve the needs of the growing LEP population in the U.S. in all major industries. </span>

&nbsp;

<b>New Immigration Trends</b>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">Asian populations rising due to immigration. The largest source of new immigrants to the United States is Asia, overtaking Latin America (including Mexico). Asians are now the only major racial or ethnic group whose numbers are rising mainly because of immigration. New immigration trends make expanding current language services a necessity to serve these populations. <a href="http://www.pewresearch.org/fact-tank/2016/03/31/10-demographic-trends-that-are-shaping-the-u-s-and-the-world/" target="_blank">Pew Research Findings</a></span>

&nbsp;
<img class="aligncenter size-large wp-image-3200" src="http://telelanguage.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/three-factors-informing-language-services-663x1024.png" alt="Alt=&quot;three factors informing language services&quot;" width="663" height="1024" />

<span style="font-weight: 400;">What does this mean for organizations looking to offer high-quality language services? Being aware of the factors that are molding the language services industry will help provide meaningful language access to different populations. Expanding your language services to include new and emerging technologies can also be an effective way to reduce costs while offering more comprehensive solutions. </span>

&nbsp;
<i><span style="font-weight: 400;">Telelanguage has been a trusted language service provider for over 25 years! We offer a complete package of language services to fit your needs: Onsite Interpretation, Over-the-Phone Interpretation, Video Remote Interpretation and Document Translation. We service multiple industries and have rigorous </span></i><a href="http://telelanguage.com/resources/interpreter-certification/"><i><span style="font-weight: 400;">training and certification programs for interpreters</span></i></a><i><span style="font-weight: 400;"> that far exceed industry standards. Our 2000+ certified interpreters are ready to speak in over 250 languages with dedicated support 24/7/365. If you are looking for a reliable language service provider or thinking about switching, </span></i><i><span style="font-weight: 400;">contact us</span></i><i><span style="font-weight: 400;"> for more <a href="http://telelanguage.com/contact-us/">information and a free demo</a>. </span></i>

&nbsp;
<p style="text-align: center;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Telelanguage offers 2000+ interpreters ready to speak in 250 languages!</span></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Call us today for a Free Demo at </span><span style="font-weight: 400;">888-983-5352</span></p>

	<item>
		<title>9 California Cities That Need Interpreter Services (Video)</title>
		<link>http://telelanguage.com/9-california-cities-interpreter-services-video/</link>
		<pubDate>Fri, 03 Feb 2017 20:53:36 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[kimberlyscamman]]></dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://telelanguage.com/?p=3207</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<span style="font-weight: 400;">California is considered a global trendsetter in areas ranging from pop culture to politics, and is the birthplace of the </span><span style="font-weight: 400;">film industry</span><span style="font-weight: 400;">, and the </span><span style="font-weight: 400;">Internet</span><span style="font-weight: 400;">. The population is greater than that of all but 34 countries of the world. The Greater Los Angeles Area is the 2nd-largest </span><span style="font-weight: 400;">metropolitan area</span><span style="font-weight: 400;"> in the United States.</span>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">California is also one of the most popular places in need of language interpretation services. According to research from </span><a href="http://www.migrationpolicy.org/article/limited-english-proficient-population-united-states"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Migration Policy Institute</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;">, as of 2013, the nationwide average of Limited-English-proficient (LEP) residents by city was approximately 8%.  Eleven states had higher percentages of LEP residents. Of the 11 states, California had the highest percentage of LEP individuals at 19% of the state population. California’s LEP population was 6.8 million individuals, accounting for 27% the total LEP population in the United States. </span>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">As a leading provider of </span><a href="http://telelanguage.com/services/"><span style="font-weight: 400;">interpretation and translation services</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;">, California is one of our </span><a href="http://telelanguage.com/interpretation-translation-locations/"><span style="font-weight: 400;">most popular</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;"> states with language services needs - and no industry is exempt. From medical and healthcare to legal and business, effective language access is important for the LEP population of the state, as well as for international business. </span>

&nbsp;
<h2>Spotlight on 9 California Cities (Video)</h2>

<iframe width="560" height="315" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/Pvw_FT7ObLE?rel=0&amp;controls=0&amp;showinfo=0" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen></iframe>
&nbsp;

<b>Los Angeles</b>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">Los Angeles, Spanish for “The Angels”, is the second most populated city in the country. </span><span style="font-weight: 400;">L.A. residents represent more than 140 countries and the city is home for those speaking 224 separate languages. </span>

<i><span style="font-weight: 400;">Key Stats:</span></i>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">Percentage of Foreign-born Persons: 39.7% (5th in the United States)</span>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">People of Mexican ancestry make up the largest ethnic group of Latinos at 31.9% of Los Angeles’ population.</span>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">The percentage of foreign-born persons in Los Angeles, California was 39.7%, ranking it 5th in the United States for foreign-born populations. (2009 Census)</span>

<em><span style="font-weight: 400;">Learn more about </span><a href="http://telelanguage.com/Los-Angeles-Long-Beach-Santa-Ana-CA/"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Los Angeles Language Access Needs</span></a></em>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">Source: </span><span style="font-weight: 400;"><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Los_Angeles#Demographics">Los Angeles</a></span>

&nbsp;

<b>Long Beach</b>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">Located on the Pacific Coast in the Greater Los Angeles Area, Long Beach is the 36th most populous city in the United States and 7th most populated city in California. The city of Long Beach is the third largest city in Southern California after Los Angeles and San Diego.</span>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">According to a report by </span><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/USA_Today"><i><span style="font-weight: 400;">USA Today</span></i></a><span style="font-weight: 400;"> in 2000, Long Beach is the most ethnically diverse large city in the United States. </span>

<i><span style="font-weight: 400;">Key Stats:</span></i>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">According to the 2010 U.S. Census Bureau, Hispanic or Latino of any race were 188,412 persons (40.8%), and 32.9% of the city’s population was of Mexican heritage.</span>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">According to a 2009 Census, the percentage of foreign-born persons in Long Beach, California was 26.9%, ranking it 20th in the United States for foreign-born populations.</span>

<em><span style="font-weight: 400;">Learn more about </span><a href="http://telelanguage.com/Los-Angeles-Long-Beach-Santa-Ana-CA/"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Long Beach Language Access Needs</span></a></em>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">Source: </span><span style="font-weight: 400;"><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Long_Beach,_California">Long Beach</a></span>

&nbsp;

<b>Santa Ana</b>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">Santa Ana is the second most populous city in Orange County, California and the 57th most-populous city in the United States.</span>

<i><span style="font-weight: 400;">Key Stats:</span></i>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">Racial makeup of Santa Ana (2010 United States Census): Hispanic or Latino of any race were 78.2%, and 10.5% were Asian.</span>

<em>Learn more about <a href="http://telelanguage.com/Los-Angeles-Long-Beach-Santa-Ana-CA/"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Santa Ana Language Access Needs</span></a></em>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">Source: </span><span style="font-weight: 400;"><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Santa_Ana,_California">Santa Ana</a></span>

&nbsp;

<b>San Francisco</b>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">San Francisco is the cultural, commercial, and financial center of Northern California. </span>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">San Francisco has a minority-majority population, as non-Hispanic whites comprise less than half of the population, 41.9% </span>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">In 2010, residents of Chinese ethnicity constituted the largest single ethnic minority group in San Francisco at 21% of the population.</span>

<i><span style="font-weight: 400;">Key Stats:</span></i>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">Immigrant Population: 1,245,521</span>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">Percent of Population: 29.50%</span>

<em><span style="font-weight: 400;">Learn More about</span> <a href="http://telelanguage.com/San-Francisco-Oakland-Fremont-CA/"><span style="font-weight: 400;">San Francisco Language Access Needs</span></a></em>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">Source: </span><span style="font-weight: 400;"><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/San_Francisco">San Francisco</a></span>

&nbsp;

<b>Oakland</b>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">Oakland is the eighth-largest city in California and the 45th largest city in the United States. Due to a steady influx of immigrants in the 20th century, along with thousands of African-American war-industry workers who relocated from the Deep South during the 1940s, Oakland is the most ethnically diverse major city in the country.</span>

<em><span style="font-weight: 400;">Learn More about</span> <a href="http://telelanguage.com/San-Francisco-Oakland-Fremont-CA/"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Oakland Language Access Needs</span></a></em>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">Source: </span><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Oakland,_California"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Oakland</span></a>

&nbsp;

<b>Fremont</b>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">Located in the San Francisco Bay Area (East Bay), Fremont is the fourth most populous city in the San Francisco Bay Area.</span>

<i><span style="font-weight: 400;">Key Stats:</span></i>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">Fremont is home to the largest population of Afghan Americans in the United States.</span>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">Mission San Jose has the highest concentration of Asian Americans in Fremont – over 50% of the population as of the 2000 census.</span>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">As of 2010 more than half the residents of Fremont were of Asian ancestry, with large populations of Chinese, Asian Indians, and Filipinos.</span>

<em><span style="font-weight: 400;">Learn More about</span> <a href="http://telelanguage.com/San-Francisco-Oakland-Fremont-CA/"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Fremont Language Access Needs</span></a></em>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">Source: </span><span style="font-weight: 400;"><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Fremont,_California">Fremont</a></span>

&nbsp;

<b>San Jose</b>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">San Jose is the third populous city in California and the tenth populous in the United States.</span>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">39% of San Jose resident are foreign-born. These include many high-tech workers from East and South Asia, Eastern European immigrants, as well as immigrants from Latin America. San Jose has the largest Vietnamese population of any city in the world outside of Vietnam.</span>

<i><span style="font-weight: 400;">Key Stats:</span></i>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">The percentage of foreign-born persons in San Jose was 39%, ranking it 6th in the United States for foreign-born populations. (2010)</span>

<em><span style="font-weight: 400;">Learn more about</span> <a href="http://telelanguage.com/San-Jose-Sunnyvale-Santa-Clara-CA/"><span style="font-weight: 400;">San Jose Language Access Needs</span></a></em>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">Source: </span><span style="font-weight: 400;"><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/San_Jose,_California">San Jose</a></span>

&nbsp;

<b>Sunnyvale</b>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">Sunnyvale is the seventh most populous city in the San Francisco Bay Area and one of the major cities comprising Silicon Valley. According to U.S. census, Sunnyvale has a large Native American population, as well as Hispanic and Latino populations.</span>

<i><span style="font-weight: 400;">Key Stats:</span></i>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">Asian Population: 40.7% </span>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">Hispanic or Latino: 18.9%</span>

<em><span style="font-weight: 400;">Learn More about</span> <a href="http://telelanguage.com/San-Jose-Sunnyvale-Santa-Clara-CA/"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Sunnyvale Language Access Needs</span></a></em>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">Source:</span> <span style="font-weight: 400;"><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sunnyvale,_California">Sunnyvale</a></span>

&nbsp;

<b>Santa Clara</b>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">Santa Clara is named after the Spanish mission that was established there in 1777. It is the ninth-most populous city in the San Francisco Bay Area, located at the center of Silicon Valley.</span>

<i><span style="font-weight: 400;">Key Stats (2010 U.S. Census):</span></i>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">Asian Population: 37.7% </span>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">Hispanic and Latino populations (19.4%) </span>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">14.6% of Santa Clara’s population was of Mexican ancestry. </span>

<em><span style="font-weight: 400;">Learn More about</span> <a href="http://telelanguage.com/San-Jose-Sunnyvale-Santa-Clara-CA/"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Santa Clara Language Access Needs</span></a></em>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">Source: </span><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Santa_Clara,_California"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Santa Clara</span></a>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">*Additional Source (1-9):</span> <a href="http://www.thedailybeast.com/galleries/2010/07/27/20-u-s-cities-with-the-most-immigrants.html"><span style="font-weight: 400;">The Daily Beast</span></a>

&nbsp;

<span style="font-weight: 400;">Telelanguage has been providing our customers with the highest quality language services since 1991 in California. As a reliable and innovative leader in the language industry, we provide interpretation and translation services to over 1,400 organizations throughout the United States – </span><a href="http://telelanguage.com/industries/"><span style="font-weight: 400;">across all industries</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;">.</span>

&nbsp;

<i><span style="font-weight: 400;">Our 2000+ certified interpreters are ready to speak in over 250 languages with dedicated support 24/7/365. If you are looking for a reliable language service provider or thinking about switching, contact us for more </span></i><a href="http://telelanguage.com/contact-us/"><i><span style="font-weight: 400;">information and a free demo</span></i></a><i><span style="font-weight: 400;">.</span></i>

	<item>
		<title>Telephone Interpreters: Improving Business-to-Business Communication</title>
		<link>http://telelanguage.com/telephone-interpreters-business-communication/</link>
		<pubDate>Fri, 10 Feb 2017 19:23:43 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[kimberlyscamman]]></dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://telelanguage.com/?p=3226</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<span style="font-weight: 400;">Whether you have an international business or you’re ready to expand your services, we live in a global market. Today, Telephonic Interpreters are an important part of growing an international company, improving business-to-business communications, and maximizing the success of global outreach. </span>

Bringing a professional telephone interpreter on conference calls for your non-English-speaking and limited-English-speaking clients ensures that you get your message across effectively, efficiently, and shows your customers that you care. </span>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">According to the </span><a href="https://www.bls.gov/ooh/media-and-communication/interpreters-and-translators.htm"><span style="font-weight: 400;">U.S. Bureau of Labor Statistics</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;">, over 61,000 people work as translators and interpreters. But not all interpreters are right for your business. So how do you select the right telephone interpreters for your conference call? </span>

&nbsp;

<h2><i><span style="font-weight: 400;">Five things to consider when looking for a telephone interpreter for business conference calls:</span></i></h2>
<img src="http://telelanguage.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/02/International-business-tele-300x300.jpg" alt="Telephone Interpreter Global Business" width="260" height="260" class="alignright size-medium wp-image-3234" /><h3>Professional Telephone Interpreters</h3>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">When it comes to expanding your business into global markets, you want to guarantee that no part of your message is left to chance. Business interpretation and translation can be highly specialized for many fields. Using an industry-certified interpreter with knowledge of your business market and specific terminology is critical to effective communication in the target language. A language service provider should offer a filter-based qualification interpreter connect feature to provide the most qualified interpreter for your situation. </span>

&nbsp;

<h3>Over-the-Phone Interpreter Protocol</h3>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">While your non-English-speaking clients may expect or be informed that interpreter will be present, you should always introduce the interpreter at the start of your conference call to avoid any confusion. Introducing your interpreter upfront will allow your clients to adjust their speaking naturally to allow for the most quality interpreting. A professional interpreter will also be aware of the etiquette of the client country and culture for sound interpretations. </span>

&nbsp;

<h3>Flexibility</h3>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">Although many international business meetings may be planned in advance, you should consider a reliable language service provider who can also provide </span><a href="http://telelanguage.com/tips-working-business-interpreter/"><span style="font-weight: 400;">business interpreters on the spot</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;"> for unexpected situations that may arise. For these situations, fast connect times is also important to keep the flow of communication and professionalism. </span>

&nbsp;

<h3>Complete Language Solution</h3>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">Using telephone interpreters for business conference calls is an efficient and cost-effective way to get your company’s message across, but not all meetings will be confined to a conference call. Choosing a language services provider with a full range of interpretation and translation options, such as Video Remote Interpreting (</span><a href="http://telelanguage.com/video-remote-interpreting-infographic/"><span style="font-weight: 400;">VRI</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;">), On-site Interpreting, and Document Translation gives businesses the ability to plan for every type of situation, make productive use of cutting-edge technology, and consistently meet client needs.</span>

&nbsp;

<h3>24/7 Accessibility</h3>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">Language barriers won’t always arise when it’s convenient. Your business may operate 9-5, but your international clients don’t. While freelance and in-house interpreters cannot be available 24/7, a dedicated language service provider should be able to provide you with the language solutions you need at any time - 24 hours a days, 7 days a week, 365 days a year. </span>

&nbsp;

<span style="font-weight: 400;">Your company’s message and communication is not something to leave to chance in a global market. You need more than just an interpreter who speaks the language of your client. When seeking telephone interpreters for business, you want to use these tips to select an interpreter or </span><a href="http://telelanguage.com/how-to-choose-language-service-provider/"><span style="font-weight: 400;">dedicated language services</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;"> provider that reflects your brand’s professionalism, can offer a complete language services solution and allows your company to grow and scale as you need it.</span>

&nbsp;

<i><span style="font-weight: 400;">Telelanguage has been a leading provider of telephonic interpretation services since 1991. We offer a complete package of language services to fit our clients’ needs: On-site Interpretation, Over-the-Phone Interpretation, Video Remote Interpretation and Document Translation. Whether you need a last-minute telephone interpreter for your conference call, an on-site appointment, or document translation, our network of 2000+ professional interpreters and translators are ready to provide understanding in 250 languages...24/7/365.  </span></i>

<i><span style="font-weight: 400;">Looking for a reliable language service provider or thinking about switching? Telelanguage can help. Contact us if you have any questions, or request a </span></i><a href="http://telelanguage.com/contact-us/"><i><span style="font-weight: 400;">free demo</span></i></a><i><span style="font-weight: 400;">. </span></i>

&nbsp;

<p style="text-align: center;"><i><span style="font-weight: 400;">Superior Language Support in 250 Languages.</span></i></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><i><span style="font-weight: 400;">Quality and expert interpretations available telephonically, face to face, and video remote!</span></i><i><span style="font-weight: 400;">
